---
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A public idea board for local ownership, clean uninstall, app accountability, and better platform stewardship."
    />
    <title>Take Back the Mac</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <a class="brand" href="/">
        <span class="brand-mark" aria-hidden="true">TBM</span>
        <span>Take Back the Mac</span>
      </a>
      <nav aria-label="Primary">
        <a href="/manifesto/">Manifesto</a>
        <a href="#ideas">Ideas</a>
        <a href="#rights">What we want</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero" id="about">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="tagline">The Mac is not vendor territory.</p>
          <h1>The machine I paid for should behave like mine.</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            A public idea board for clean uninstall, visible app footprints,
            honest background behavior, App Store stewardship, and devices that
            treat their owners like owners.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button primary" href="#idea-form">Add an idea</a>
            <a class="button secondary" href="/manifesto/">Read the manifesto</a>
            <a class="button secondary" href="#rights">What we want</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="manifesto-overview" aria-labelledby="manifesto-heading">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <h2 id="manifesto-heading">Manifesto</h2>
          <p>
            This is a simple argument: Apple has enough control to make the
            Mac cleaner, safer, and more respectful. If it wants that control,
            it should use it to defend the user.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="manifesto-card">
          <p>
            The Mac should be a trusted personal computer, not a place where
            every app leaves a private mess and every owner becomes a part-time
            system administrator. Clean uninstall, visible app footprints,
            honest background behavior, and a better App Store are not power
            user luxuries. They are table stakes for an owned device.
          </p>
          <a class="button primary" href="/manifesto/">Read the manifesto</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="ideas-section" id="ideas" aria-labelledby="ideas-heading">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <h2 id="ideas-heading">Idea board</h2>
          <p>
            Add a concrete thing Apple should fix. Upvote what should rise.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="ideas-shell">
          <form class="idea-form" id="idea-form">
            <h3>Add an idea</h3>
            <label>
              <span>Title</span>
              <input
                name="title"
                type="text"
                maxlength="120"
                required
                placeholder="Uninstall should show every file an app created"
              />
            </label>
            <label>
              <span>Details</span>
              <textarea
                name="body"
                maxlength="1200"
                rows="5"
                placeholder="What should Apple change? What pain does it remove?"
              ></textarea>
            </label>
            <div class="form-row">
              <label>
                <span>Category</span>
                <select name="category">
                  <option>Uninstall</option>
                  <option>Background</option>
                  <option>App Store</option>
                  <option>Services</option>
                  <option>Privacy</option>
                  <option>iOS</option>
                  <option>Mac</option>
                  <option>Other</option>
                </select>
              </label>
              <label>
                <span>Email</span>
                <input
                  name="email"
                  type="email"
                  maxlength="254"
                  required
                  autocomplete="email"
                  placeholder="you@example.com"
                />
              </label>
            </div>
            <label>
              <span>Name optional</span>
              <input name="author" type="text" maxlength="80" placeholder="Your name" />
            </label>
            <button class="button primary" type="submit">Submit idea</button>
            <p class="status" id="idea-form-status" aria-live="polite"></p>
          </form>

          <div class="ideas-panel">
            <div class="ideas-toolbar">
              <h3>Ideas</h3>
              <div class="segmented" aria-label="Sort ideas">
                <button type="button" data-idea-sort="top" aria-pressed="true">Top</button>
                <button type="button" data-idea-sort="new" aria-pressed="false">New</button>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="idea-list" id="idea-list" aria-live="polite">
              <p class="empty">Loading ideas...</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="rights-section" id="rights" aria-labelledby="rights-heading">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <h2 id="rights-heading">What we want</h2>
          <p>
            The first demands are here. Upvote what Apple should make real
            first.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rights-list" id="rights-list"></div>
        <div class="demand-callout">
          <div>
            <h3>Add your own demand</h3>
            <p>
              If something is missing, add it to the idea board. Specific
              demands beat vague frustration.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a class="button primary" href="#idea-form">Add a demand</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <span>That's a Mac, Jack.</span>
      <a href="https://paulwelty.com">Started by Paul Welty</a>
      <a href="https://marco.org/2026/04/01/letter-to-john-ternus">Inspired in part by Marco Arment's letter to John Ternus</a>
    </footer>

    <script src="/app.js" type="module"></script>
  </body>
</html>
